flowRoot.flowPara: Sidebar is shown when there are manually created playlists.
Removable media appears pinned to the top of the grid.
You could miss the devices if you're in view other than albums. Conceptually, devices don't belong to albums.
import button would be shown for downloads, selection from files, removable devices.
Removable media devices are displayed as info bars at the top of the content area - these are displayed for all views (artists, songs, etc).
While this works in terms of the logic, it feels rather heavy and clunky visually. The bar would be quite a big distraction when you're not engaged with the removable device.

text.tspan: USB Stick contains 15 tracks that aren't in your library

flowRoot.flowPara: "Home" view provides a dynamic window on to your music. It contains removable devices when they're present, downloaded music when that's present, and other smart playlists (the playlists view would just show manually created playlists). A better name than "Home" is probably required for this.
There's some overlap between "suggestions" on the one hand and album/artist/song views on the other (if they're ordered by recently added"). We would need to decide on the best approach for that.
